# Chat windows and context

This repo has **flow-scoped context packs** under [`.cursor/context/`](.cursor/context/README.md).

## For the human

- Open a **new Cursor Chat (or Composer)** per major flow (e.g. “Smart Actions only”, “Campaign API only”).
- At the start of the chat, **attach** the right file with `@`, e.g. `@.cursor/context/03-campaign-builder.md`.
- For cross-cutting changes (same huge file, two flows), use **one chat** and mention both context files, or **serialize** work to reduce merge conflicts.

## For the agent

- When the user names an area (dashboard, reminders, offers, generation, menu), **prefer** reading or following the matching `.cursor/context/*.md` so file lists and boundaries stay accurate.
- Do not expand scope into unrelated flows without the user asking; suggest a **separate chat** + context file for the other area.
